{"title":"TTL expiry walkthrough","gitnotes":1,"type":"html","body":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<style>\n  :root { --bg:#0e1218; --fg:#dce4ee; --muted:#7d8a99; --accent:#7ee787; --card:#151b24; --border:#2a3441; }\n  body { font:15px/1.55 system-ui,sans-serif; background:var(--bg); color:var(--fg); margin:0; padding:1.5rem 2rem; max-width:50rem; }\n  h1 { font-size:1.3rem; margin:0 0 .5rem; }\n  label { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:.5rem; cursor:pointer; color:var(--muted); font-size:.9rem; margin-bottom:1rem; }\n  .view { background:var(--card); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:8px; padding:1rem 1.2rem; min-height:8rem; }\n  a { color:#79c0ff; }\n  .step { margin:.4rem 0; }\n  .hidden { display:none; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>TTL lazy vs proactive expiry</h1>\n<label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"toggle\"> Show line-level detail</label>\n<div class=\"view\">\n  <div id=\"brief\">\n    <p class=\"step\">1. <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/ttl.ts#R11-R13\">Constructor</a> rejects non-positive default TTL.</p>\n    <p class=\"step\">2. <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/ttl.ts#R15-R17\">set()</a> stamps <code>expiresAt = now + ttlMs</code>.</p>\n    <p class=\"step\">3. <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/ttl.ts#R19-R26\">get()</a> deletes expired entries on read (lazy).</p>\n    <p class=\"step\">4. <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/ttl.ts#R28-R37\">prune()</a> sweeps all stale keys in one pass.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"deep\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <p>Lazy expiry keeps hot paths cheap — stale keys that are never read consume memory until <code>prune()</code> or the next <code>get</code>.</p>\n    <p>For the GitNotes service worker analogue: pair TTL cache with a periodic alarm to call <code>prune()</code> so negative-cache entries don't linger.</p>\n    <p>Per-key override via optional <code>ttlMs</code> argument on <code>set</code> supports short-lived error responses vs long-lived blob SHAs.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<script>\ndocument.getElementById('toggle').addEventListener('change', function(e) {\n  document.getElementById('deep').classList.toggle('hidden', !e.target.checked);\n});\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"}
